detail.name: CL_DEVICE_VENDOR
detail.help: Vendor name string.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_TYPE
detail.help: The OpenCL device type. Currently supported values are one of or a combination of: CL_DEVICE_TYPE_CPU, CL_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU, CL_DEVICE_TYPE_ACCELERATOR, or CL_DEVICE_TYPE_DEFAULT.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_ADDRESS_BITS
detail.help: The default compute device address space size specified as an unsigned integer value in bits. Currently supported values are 32 or 64 bits.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_EXTENSIONS
detail.value: cl_khr_global_int32_base_atomics cl_khr_global_int32_extended_atomics cl_khr_local_int32_base_atomics cl_khr_local_int32_extended_atomics cl_khr_fp64 cl_khr_byte_addressable_store cl_khr_icd cl_khr_gl_sharing cl_nv_compiler_options cl_nv_device_attribute_query cl_nv_pragma_unroll cl_nv_copy_opts cl_khr_gl_event cl_nv_create_buffer cl_khr_int64_base_atomics cl_khr_int64_extended_atomics cl_kernel_attribute_nv
detail.help: Returns a list of extension names

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_VERSION
detail.help: OpenCL version string. Returns the OpenCL version supported by the device. This version string has the following format:: OpenCL<space><major_version.minor_version><space><vendor-specific information> The major_version.minor_version value returned will be 1.0.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_GLOBAL_MEM_CACHE_SIZE
detail.help: Size of global memory cache in bytes.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_GLOBAL_ MEM_CACHELINE_SIZE
detail.help: Size of global memory cache line in bytes.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_GLOBAL_MEM_SIZE
detail.help: Size of global device memory in bytes.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE
detail.help: Size of local device memory in bytes.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE
detail.help: Maximum number of work-items in a work-group executing a kernel on a single compute unit, using the data parallel execution model. (Refer to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel). The minimum value is 1.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_ITEM_DIMENSIONS
detail.help: Maximum dimensions that specify the global and local work-item IDs used by the data parallel execution model. (Refer to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel). The minimum value is 3 for devices that are not of type CL_DEVICE_TYPE_CUSTOM.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_ITEM_SIZES
detail.help: Maximum number of work-items that can be specified in each dimension of the work-group to clEnqueueNDRangeKernel.Returns n size_t entries, where n is the value returned by the query for CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_ITEM_DIMENSIONS.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_MEM_BASE_ADDR_ALIGN
detail.help: The minimum value is the size (in bits) of the largest OpenCL built-in data type supported by the device (long16 in FULL profile, long16 or int16 in EMBEDDED profile) for devices that are not of type CL_DEVICE_TYPE_CUSTOM.

detail.name: CL_DEVICE_PREFERRED_VECTOR_WIDTH_CHAR
detail.help: Preferred native vector width size for built-in scalar types that can be put into vectors. The vector width is defined as the number of scalar elements that can be stored in the vector.
